turn.0: Hi, I'm your automated assistant. I can answer your questions about Digestate.
turn.2: Digestate  Digestate is the material remaining after the anaerobic digestion of a biodegradable feedstock.
turn.3: What else did you find interesting?
turn.4: Anaerobic digestion produces two main products: digestate and biogas.
turn.5: Is there anything else I should know?
turn.6: Digestate is produced both by acidogenesis and methanogenesis and each has different characteristics.
turn.7: What are some of the characteristics?
turn.8: Acidogenic digestate is fibrous and consists of structural plant matter including lignin and cellulose.
turn.9: Is there anything else different about it?
turn.10: Acidogenic digestate has high moisture retention properties.
turn.12: The digestate may also contain minerals and remnants of bacteria.
